      "source": "\n\n// Base class. Handles method and parameters. Waiting callback\nclass Request {\n  // Let others know our waiting state\n\n  // RPC call name\n  constructor(method, param, waitingHandler) {\n    this._waiting = false;\n\n    this._method = method;\n    this._param = param || {};\n    this._waitingHandler = waitingHandler;\n  }\n  // If we're waiting for a response\n\n  // RPC parameters\n\n\n  get param() {\n    return this._param;\n  }\n  get method() {\n    return this._method;\n  }\n\n  updateWaiting(waiting) {\n    this._waiting = waiting;\n    this._waitingHandler(waiting);\n  }\n}\n// Incoming and outgoing requests that are in a session\n\n\nclass IncomingRequest extends Request {\n  // Callback in the incomingCallMap\n  constructor(method, param, response, waitingHandler, handler) {\n    super(method, param, waitingHandler);\n\n    this._handler = handler;\n    this._response = response;\n  }\n\n  _cleanup() {\n    this.updateWaiting(true // We just responded to the server so now we're waiting\n    );\n  }\n\n  result(...args) {\n    this._response && this._response.result(...args);\n    this._cleanup();\n  }\n\n  error(...args) {\n    this._response && this._response.error(...args);\n    this._cleanup();\n  }\n\n  handle() {\n    this.updateWaiting(false // we just got a response from the server so we're no longer waiting\n\n    // Note we pass ourself to the handler and not the raw response. This allows us to cleanup\n    );this._handler(this.param, this);\n  }\n}\n\nclass OutgoingRequest extends Request {\n  // Callback when we've gotten a response\n  constructor(method, param, callback, waitingHandler, invoke) {\n    super(method, param, waitingHandler);\n    this._invoke = invoke;\n    this._callback = callback;\n  }\n  // How we make calls\n\n\n  send() {\n    this.updateWaiting(true);\n    this._invoke && this._invoke(this.method, this.param, (err, data) => this._sendCallback(err, data));\n  }\n\n  _sendCallback(err, data) {\n    this.updateWaiting(false);\n    this._callback && this._callback(err, data);\n  }\n}\n\nexport { IncomingRequest, OutgoingRequest };"

      "source": "var _extends = Object.assign || function (target) { for (var i = 1; i < arguments.length; i++) { var source = arguments[i]; for (var key in source) { if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(source, key)) { target[key] = source[key]; } } } return target; };\n\nimport { IncomingRequest, OutgoingRequest } from './request';\n\nimport { ConstantsStatusCode } from '../constants/types/flow-types';\nimport { rpcLog } from './index.platform';\nimport { RPCError } from '../util/errors';\n\n// A session is a series of calls back and forth tied together with a single sessionID\nclass Session {\n\n  // Outstanding requests\n\n  // If you want to know about being cancelled\n\n  // Tell engine we're done\n\n  // Map of methods => callbacks\n\n  // If true this session exists forever\n\n  // Name of the start method, just to help debug\n\n  // Start callback so we can cancel our own callback\n\n\n  // Allow us to make calls\n  constructor(sessionID, incomingCallMap, waitingHandler, invoke, endHandler, cancelHandler, dangling = false) {\n    this._seqIDResponded = {};\n    this._outgoingRequests = [];\n    this._incomingRequests = [];\n\n    this._id = sessionID;\n    this._incomingCallMap = incomingCallMap || {};\n    this._waitingHandler = waitingHandler;\n    this._invoke = invoke;\n    this._endHandler = endHandler;\n    this._cancelHandler = cancelHandler;\n    this._dangling = dangling;\n  }\n  // Sequence IDs we've seen. Value is true if we've responded (often we get cancel after we've replied)\n\n  // Let the outside know we're waiting\n\n  // Our id\n\n\n  set id(sessionID) {\n    throw new Error(\"Can't set sessionID\");\n  }\n  get id() {\n    return this._id;\n  }\n  get dangling() {\n    return this._dangling;\n  }\n\n  // Make a waiting handler for the request. We add additional data before calling the parent waitingHandler\n  // and do internal bookkeeping if the request is done\n  _makeWaitingHandler(isOutgoing, method, seqid) {\n    return waiting => {\n      rpcLog('engineInternal', 'waiting state change', { id: this.id, waiting, method, this: this, seqid }\n      // Call the outer handler with all the params it needs\n      );this._waitingHandler && this._waitingHandler(waiting, method, this._id\n\n      // Request is finished, do cleanup\n      );if (!waiting) {\n        const requests = isOutgoing ? this._outgoingRequests : this._incomingRequests;\n        const idx = requests.findIndex(r => r.method === method);\n        if (idx !== -1) {\n          // Mark us as responded\n          if (seqid) {\n            this._seqIDResponded[String(seqid)] = true;\n          }\n          // Remove from our list\n          requests.splice(idx, 1);\n        }\n      }\n    };\n  }\n\n  cancel() {\n    if (this._cancelHandler) {\n      this._cancelHandler(this);\n    } else if (this._startCallback) {\n      this._startCallback(new RPCError('Received RPC cancel for session', ConstantsStatusCode.sccanceled));\n    }\n\n    this.end();\n  }\n\n  end() {\n    this._endHandler && this._endHandler(this);\n  }\n\n  // Start the session normally. Tells engine we're done at the end\n  start(method, param, callback) {\n    this._startMethod = method;\n    this._startCallback = callback;\n\n    // When this request is done the session is done\n    const wrappedCallback = (...args) => {\n      this._startCallback && this._startCallback(...args);\n      this._startCallback = null;\n      this.end();\n    };\n\n    // Add the sessionID\n    const wrappedParam = _extends({}, param, {\n      sessionID: this.id\n    });\n\n    rpcLog('engineInternal', 'session start call', { id: this.id, method, this: this });\n    const outgoingRequest = new OutgoingRequest(method, wrappedParam, wrappedCallback, this._makeWaitingHandler(true, method), this._invoke);\n    this._outgoingRequests.push(outgoingRequest);\n    outgoingRequest.send();\n  }\n\n  // We have an incoming call tied to a sessionID, called only by engine\n  incomingCall(method, param, response) {\n    rpcLog('engineInternal', 'session incoming call', { id: this.id, method, this: this, response });\n    const handler = this._incomingCallMap[method];\n\n    if (!handler) {\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    if (response && response.seqid) {\n      this._seqIDResponded[String(response.seqid)] = false;\n    }\n\n    const waitingHandler = this._makeWaitingHandler(false, method, response && response.seqid);\n    const incomingRequest = new IncomingRequest(method, param, response, waitingHandler, handler);\n    this._incomingRequests.push(incomingRequest);\n    incomingRequest.handle();\n\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Tell engine if we can handle the cancelled call\n  hasSeqID(seqID) {\n    if (__DEV__) {\n      if (this._seqIDResponded.hasOwnProperty(String(seqID))) {\n        console.log('Cancelling seqid found, current session state', this);\n      }\n    }\n    return this._seqIDResponded.hasOwnProperty(String(seqID));\n  }\n}\n\nexport default Session;"

Wrapped to ensure its called once\nfunction _makeOnceOnly(f) {\n  let once = false;\n  return (...args) => {\n    if (once) {\n      rpcLog('engineInternal', 'ignoring multiple result calls', { args });\n    } else {\n      once = true;\n      f(...args);\n    }\n  };\n}\n\n// Wrapped to add logging\nfunction _makeLogged(f, type, logTitle, extraInfo, titleFromArgs) {\n  if (printRPC) {\n    return (...args) => {\n      rpcLog(type, titleFromArgs ? titleFromArgs(...args) : logTitle, _extends({}, extraInfo, { args }));\n      f(...args);\n    };\n  } else {\n    return f;\n  }\n}\n\n// Wrapped to make time delayed functions to test timing issues\nfunction _makeDelayed(f, amount) {\n  if (__DEV__ && amount > 0) {\n    return (...args) => {\n      localLog('%c[RPC Delay call]', 'color: red');\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        f(...args);\n      }, amount);\n    };\n  } else {\n    return f;\n  }\n}\n\n// We basically always delay/log/ensure once all the calls back and forth\nfunction _wrap(f, logType, amount, logTitle, logInfo) {\n  const logged = _makeLogged(f, logType, logTitle, logInfo);\n  const delayed = _makeDelayed(logged, amount);\n  const onceOnly = _makeOnceOnly(delayed);\n  return onceOnly;\n}\n\n// Logging for rpcs\nfunction rpcLog(type, title, info) {\n  if (!printRPC) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const prefix = {\n    engineInternal: '[engine]',\n    engineToServer: '[engine] ->',\n    serverToEngine: '[engine] <-'\n  }[type];\n  const style = {\n    engineInternal: 'color: purple',\n    engineToServer: 'color: blue',\n    serverToEngine: 'color: green'\n  }[type];\n\n  requestIdleCallback(() => {\n    localLog(`%c${prefix}`, style, title, info);\n  }, { timeout: 1e3 });\n}\n\nclass TransportShared extends RobustTransport {\n  // $FlowIssue\n  constructor(opts, connectCallback, disconnectCallback, incomingRPCCallback, writeCallback) {\n    const hooks = {\n      connected: () => {\n        // $FlowIssue complains that this might be null\n        this.needsConnect = false;\n        connectCallback && connectCallback();\n      },\n      eof: () => {\n        disconnectCallback && disconnectCallback();\n      }\n    };\n\n    super(_extends({ hooks }, opts));\n\n    if (writeCallback) {\n      this.writeCallback = writeCallback;\n    }\n    if (incomingRPCCallback) {\n      // delay the call back to us\n      const handler = payload => {\n        this._injectInstrumentedResponse(payload);\n        incomingRPCCallback(payload);\n      };\n\n      this.set_generic_handler(_makeDelayed(_makeLogged(handler, 'serverToEngine', 'incoming', null, args => `incoming: ${args.method}`), KEYBASE_RPC_DELAY_RESULT));\n    }\n  }\n\n  // add delay / logging / multiple call checking\n  _injectInstrumentedResponse(payload) {\n    if (!payload || !payload.response) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const oldResponse = payload && payload.response;\n\n    if (payload && oldResponse) {\n      const calls = ['cancel', 'error', 'result'];\n\n      // Can't use {...} here due to react-native not doing object.assign on objects w/ proto chains\n      payload.response = {};\n      Object.keys(oldResponse).forEach(key => {\n        payload.response[key] = oldResponse[key];\n      });\n\n      calls.forEach(call => {\n        payload.response[call] = _wrap((...args) => {\n          oldResponse[call](...args);\n        }, 'engineToServer', KEYBASE_RPC_DELAY, call, { payload });\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  unwrap_incoming_error(err) {\n    // eslint-disable-line camelcase\n    if (!err) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    if (typeof err === 'object') {\n      return err;\n    } else {\n      return new Error(JSON.stringify(err));\n    }\n  }\n\n  invoke(arg, cb) {\n    // args needs to be wrapped as an array for some reason so lets just do that here\n    const wrappedArgs = _extends({}, arg, {\n      args: [arg.args || {}]\n    });\n\n    const wrappedInvoke = _wrap(args => {\n      super.invoke(args, _wrap((err, data) => {\n        cb(err, data);\n      }, 'serverToEngine', KEYBASE_RPC_DELAY_RESULT, `received ${arg.method}`));\n    }, 'engineToServer', KEYBASE_RPC_DELAY, `sent ${arg.method}`);\n\n    wrappedInvoke(wrappedArgs);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction sharedCreateClient(nativeTransport) {\n  const rpcClient = new RpcClient(nativeTransport);\n\n  if (rpcClient.transport.needsConnect) {\n    rpcClient.transport.connect(err => {\n      if (err != null) {\n        console.log('Error in connecting to transport rpc:', err);\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  return rpcClient;\n}\n\nexport { TransportShared, sharedCreateClient, rpcLog };"
